# Latest prompt for remembering context: 
I am working on a React + TypeScript landing page project for a digital paintings / museum-style website.

Tech stack:

React + TypeScript (Vite)
Chakra UI
React Router
Framer Motion (for page transitions)

Current UI state:

Landing page has a museum-like aesthetic (not e-commerce)
Animated geometric background (circles, squares, triangles)
includes subtle mouse parallax movement
shapes are responsive (smaller on mobile)
only visible in hero section
Hero section has:
soft glowing background spotlight
centered title + description + CTA buttons
slightly reduced height (~70vh)
Navbar:
glassmorphism style
login and signup buttons navigate to /login and /signup
Carousel:
infinite horizontal scrolling
8 paintings duplicated for smooth loop
all images have same default state (no “featured image”)
default: slightly scaled down + reduced opacity
hover: scale up + full opacity + shadow + rotation reset
Feature cards:
glass style cards
hover lift animation
scroll-in animation using Framer Motion
Global style:
smooth hover micro-interactions everywhere
consistent transition timing (~0.2–0.35s)
Page transitions:
Framer Motion fade + slight vertical motion between routes

Design goal:

modern digital museum / Apple-style landing page
smooth, minimal, atmospheric UI with subtle motion
no heavy UI clutter, focus on elegance and flow

Current progress stage:

Step 7B completed (page transitions)
Step 7A completed (micro-interactions)
background + hero + navbar + carousel + feature cards implemented

Next likely step:

